title: Grateful Dead Live at Capital Centre on 1987-09-12
description: Hell In A Bucket, Loser, Me & My Uncle, Big River, Ramble On Rose, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, Hey Pocky Way, Cassidy, Might As Well Cumberland Blues, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Women Are Smarter-> Drums-> Jam-> Truckin'-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: One More Saturday Night, E: Black Muddy River

reviews.review_text:
Morning Dew The Morning Dew deserves an honorable mention along with of course MSG's 9-18-87 as you all well know. . Take a chance and listen to this as well. Don't be scared, but " i guess it does'nt matter anyway" The boys were "ON" whole tour.

PS: I would love for someone on this great site to add the night before this. 9-11-87. Mickey's B-Day The 2nd set Sugaree needs to be heard...The whole show...

I forgot how smokin' this show was... From the get go, this show smokes.  Jerry is on fire, and the whole band seemed to be having a great time onstage this night...wish I could say the same thing for the security outside the place...what a bunch of grumps...

Anyways, this show is definitely worth your attention for each and every performance contained within it.  

A gem of a jewel...

1000Watts of power This show was pure energy for everyone, the band, us, the lame security force.  Every song was rocking.  From Space - BMR, everything fit very nice.  Lots of energy songs and the dew, gee whiz.  Never had such a good time..........

Great Show I was lucky enough to be at this show, which was an above average for the fall tour.  The Cumberland opening of the second set was cool, and the band played well all night.  A note as to the security.  I was in a very, very long line waiting to get in.  It was taking forever because of the mandatory body cavity searchs taking place inside.  The show was about to start, and people started crowing around the doors.  A female police officer came wading in on a horse.  I got pushed to the left (right at the entrance to the door), and the poeople on the other side were being mishandled by the horse's ass (not the cop).  A nice young Deadhead said, "Hey, be careful before someone gets hurt."  The policewoman wacked him across the nose with her nightstick, spraying blood everywhere.  I kid you not.  Luckily for me, the horse wacked me through the doors and into a truely memorable show.

I was there, no sweat... This was one very high quality show. I had no bad experiences with police, although I do recall that mounted police were prevalent that whole weekend. But back to the show.... This is the show that made me really love the work that Brent was doing. He injected so much energy and vocal depth to this show that I was amazed. I guess that it was probably myself that had overlooked his contributions until that night, but never thereafter. I sure miss his "heart of steel."

Who was hiding this dew? Deadbase lists the "top" 10 Dews, 5/8/77, 9/18/87 are up there. How is this one not? I think cause people are quick to forget this show because of 9/18. This soundboard is fantastic, it has a little touch of the audience in it so you can really feel it. I will say it..this dew is top 3 people!!!

The 87 show I've been waiting for Finally, after listening to many subpar shows from 1987, I have a show that is worthy of more than 3 stars. Solid all around, and contains one of the better Morning Dews. No major flubs, Jerry's voice is on, and the playing seems inspired. Not transcendent, so no 5, but a quality 4.

Nice Spanish Jam What a great show!!  It really takes me back to that night where I was dancing so hard that by the set break I was drenched.  Ahhh well maybe it was the ecstasy?  This could easily be my favorite show (that I was at).  The second set is nearly perfect.  Highly recommended!!
9-12-87 Nice show. Excellent sound quality. These '87 shows are often overlooked but after Jerry's near death experience in '86 he cleaned up (for a while) and sounded so fresh and youthful.
My First Show Sounds great. Bummer stream only, but at least it's accessible.
